   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN"># Number of supporting facilities functioned to support private sector business in investing in Agriculture NDC measures
#  Number of trainings introduced to support businesses in development of pipeline investment projects toward climate smart and green businesses
# Number of business models in the supply chains for Agriculture get supported by NDC supporting facilities
# Number of firms in agriculture supply chains get access to finance and supporting facilities from MPI SME Fund 
# Number of Data Hub established to support SME in green supply chain 
# Number of Private Sector Advisory Network established link with NDC IP
# Investment Forum for NDC as part of NDC IP
# Number of firms registered climate actions 
# Transparency platform established for large emitter firms/supply chains, particularly those who are highly consuming the energy and environment resources</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2019">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN"># No supporting facilities functioned to support private sector business in investing in Agriculture NDC measures
# Businesses are lack of capacity to development of pipeline investment projects toward climate smart and green businesses
# Not available model proven as green supply chains for Agriculture as part of NDC
# Business lack of access or have limit funding for green business or climate actions, including lack of financial and technical supporting facilities from Government
# Lack of data to support private sector in taking decision for climate action/green supply chain 
# No Private Sector Advisory Network established 
# Limit Forum for private sector to participate into NDC Implementation platform
# No platform to track firms  in taking their climate actions 
# No transparency mechanism established for large emitter firms/supply chains, particularly those who are highly consuming the energy and environment resources</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">- 01 Number of supporting facilities functioned to support private sector business in investing in Agriculture NDC measures
- 01 Number of trainings introduced to support businesses in development of pipeline investment projects toward climate smart and green businesses
- 01 Private Sector Advisory Network established link with NDC IP</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">- 01 supporting facility to promote Innovative approaches to engage cooperatives and farmer groups in green solutions are promoted explored via green shrimp contests and application of livestreaming in promotion for green products to high end domestic markets 
- 01 supply chain mapping and roadmap for green agriculture commodities undertaken. This is complimented by the recommendation from the project to establish an integrated Agriculture Data Hub to tackle the shortcomings of quality, availability and transparency of agriculture data for greening agriculture commodities
- 01 meeting of Private Sector Advisory Network established link with NDC IP organised by UNDP-MARD on &#x201C;Accelerating Agriculture Business Towards Low-Emission and Climate-Resilient Pathways in Viet Nam&#x201D;. Participants were from MARD ICD, PSAV, Crop Department, Binh Thuan People Committee, Ham Thuan Nam Districts, Binh Thuan Agriculture Department, TE-Food, Lavifood (leading fruit processing firms), Farmers from Cooperatives of Dragon fruits, IFC representative, SNV, etc</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
